<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Jadon Sancho is adamant that he will sign for Manchester United before the transfer window closes on October 5.</p>

<p>The 20-year-old winger has called on his advisors to 'pull out all the stops' in order to finalise a deal with the Red Devils.</p>

<p>Borussia Dortmund are also willing to allow Sancho to join United, despite publicly insisting that he would not be leaving the club during the 2020-21 campaign.</p>

<p>Jadon Sancho is adamant he will sign for Manchester United before the October 5 deadline</p>

<p>Sancho has long been linked with a move to Old Trafford, but sources close to Dortmund have confirmed that the England winger is working on solidifying terms with the Premier League club.</p>

<p>According to The Sun they said: 'He [Sancho] wants this deal done.</p>

<p>'He's told his agent and various advisors to do all they can to make it happen.</p>

<p>'They are pushing for him.'</p>

<p>Ole Gunnar Solskjaer is said to be confident in attaining Sancho's signature, but negotiations are still underway.</p>

<p>The two parties are believed to have held discussions with intermediaries on Tuesday but United are still refusing to meet Dortmund's demand for £108m.</p>

<p>A source close to Dortmund said: 'There's a bit of a stand off going on... it's a case of who blinks first.</p>

<p>'Will United up the offer or will Dortmund accept a lower bid?</p>

<p>'The Red Devils are considering making a final bid for the young star on Wednesday in the hope of forcing the deal across the line.</p>

<p>Ole Gunnar Solskjaer is confident in singing Sancho, but negotiations are still underway</p>

<p>United could move for Barcelona's Ousmane Dembele if they abandon attempts for Sancho</p>

<p>Sancho enjoyed another electric season for the German outfit in 2019-20, scoring 20 goals and providing 18 assists to confirm his name as one of the most talented stars in world football.</p>

<p>United are said to be lining up replacements in case they fail to land him, with Solskjaer desperate to secure a new winger. </p>

<p>The Red Devils could move for Barcelona's Ousmane Dembele if they abandon attempts to sign Sancho. </p>

<p>United sources confirmed that the 23-year-old Frenchman has been discussed although any move is likely to be on loan.  </p>
